To run this code on linux system, use command

python3 rbf.py


Required packages : pandas, matplotlib, numpy.

The program will save graphs for different values of K and learn rate as .png files in the current folder. The names of the file are indicative of the parameters K and learn rate.

By default the program uses different variance for the clusters. To use the fixed guassian width, change variable fixedGuassianWidth in main function to True from False. 